, "Palghat Mani Iyer | Palghat T. S. Mani Iyer (1912–1981) was one of the leading mridangists in the field of Carnatic music. He was awarded the Madras Music Academy's Sangeetha Kalanidhi in 1966. Mani Iyer was the first mridangist to win the Sangeetha Kalanidhi and Padmabhushan awards of the Government of India. He received the Sangeet Natak Akademi Award in 1956.", 'Rao Bahaddur Ramanath Iyer Award | The Rao Bahaddur Ramanath Iyer Award was instituted to promote the cotton research work, in India. This is being bestowed by the Indian Society for Cotton Improvement. Mumbai. Ramanath Iyer was a prominent cotton breeder in Tamil nadu, during the early part of 20th Century.'], 'question': 'R. Pichumani Iyer was the winner of a prestigious award given for excellence in which field ?', 'reasoning': 'R. Pichumani Iyer is described as a veena vidwan, which means he was an expert in playing the veena, a traditional Indian musical instrument. He is mentioned to have won the prestigious Kalaimamani award, so the question is asking about the field for which he won this award.', 'search_query': 'What is the Kalaimamani award and in which field is it given?'}) (input_keys=None)]

'generate_answer.predict' predictor demos: [Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Tom McCarthy (ice hockey, born 1960) | Thomas Joseph McCarthy (born July 31, 1960) is a Canadian retired professional ice hockey player. He played 460 games in the National Hockey League for the Minnesota North Stars and Boston Bruins. McCarthy is currently the head coach of the HSC Csíkszereda of the Romanian Hockey League (RHL).', 'Tom McCarthy (director) | Thomas Joseph "Tom" McCarthy (born June 7, 1966) is an American film director, screenwriter, and actor who has appeared in several films, including "Meet the Parents" and "Good Night, and Good Luck", and television series such as "The Wire", "Boston Public", "Law & Order", and the Hallmark Hall of Fame presentation of "Saint Maybe".', "Tom McCarthy (sportscaster) | Tom McCarthy (born July 5, 1968 in Jersey City, New Jersey) is an American sports broadcaster. He is the play-by-play announcer for Philadelphia Phillies television broadcasts and also calls National Football League games for Westwood One and called select NFL games for CBS beginning in 2014 after filling for Sam Rosen in week 6 in 2013. McCarthy has also been the play-by-play voice of Saint Joseph's University men's and women's basketball teams.", 'Héctor Babenco | Héctor Eduardo Babenco (February 7, 1946July 13, 2016) was an Argentine-born Brazilian film director, screenwriter, producer and actor. He worked in several countries including Argentina, Brazil and the United States. His best known films are "Pixote" (1980), "Kiss of the Spider Woman" (1985), "Ironweed" (1987), "At Play in the Fields of the Lord" (1990) and "Carandiru" (2003).'], 'question': 'Héctor Babenco and Tom McCarthy are both what?', 'reasoning': 'To answer the question, I need to identify if both Héctor Babenco and Tom McCarthy share an occupation. From the given information:\n- Héctor Babenco is an Argentine-born Brazilian film director, screenwriter, and producer.\n- Tom McCarthy (ice hockey) is a retired professional ice hockey player.\n- Tom McCarthy (director) is an American film director, screenwriter, and actor.\n- Tom McCarthy (sportscaster) is an American sports broadcaster.\n\nAmong these, we have two individuals with direct information on being film directors: Héctor Babenco and Tom McCarthy (director).', 'answer': 'film director'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Bill Melendez | José Cuauhtémoc Meléndez (November 15, 1916 – September 2, 2008), known as Bill Melendez, was a Mexican American character animator, film director, voice artist and producer, known for his cartoons for Walt Disney Productions (working on four Disney films "Pinocchio", "Fantasia", "Dumbo" and "Bambi"), Warner Bros. Cartoons, UPA and the "Peanuts" series. Melendez provided the voices of Snoopy and Woodstock in the latter as well.', 'A Boy Named Charlie Brown | A Boy Named Charlie Brown is a 1969 American animated comedy-drama film, produced by Cinema Center Films, distributed by National General Pictures, and directed by Bill Melendez, it is the first feature film based on the "Peanuts" comic strip. It was also the final time that Peter Robbins voiced the character of Charlie Brown (Robbins had voiced the role for all the Peanuts television specials up to that point, starting with the debut of the specials, "A Charlie Brown Christmas") in 1965.', 'Frosty Returns | Frosty Returns is an animated Christmas television special starring Jonathan Winters as the narrator and John Goodman as the voice of Frosty the Snowman. The special was directed by Bill Melendez and Evert Brown and features music by Mark Mothersbaugh. It first aired in 1992 on CBS.', 'The Peanuts Movie | The Peanuts Movie (known in some countries as Snoopy and Charlie Brown: The Peanuts Movie) is a 2015 American 3D computer-animated comedy film produced by Blue Sky Studios and distributed by 20th Century Fox, based on Charles M. Schulz\'s comic strip "Peanuts". The film is directed by Steve Martino and written by Craig and Bryan Schulz (Schulz\'s son and grandson, respectively), and Cornelius Uliano, and stars the voices of Noah Schnapp as Charlie Brown and, via archival recordings, Bill Melendez as Snoopy and Woodstock. It is the fifth full-length "Peanuts" film, and the first feature film in 35 years. It commemorates the 65th anniversary of the comic strip and the 50th anniversary of the TV special "A Charlie Brown Christmas", and was released on November 6, 2015.'], 'question': 'Which character did Bill Melendez voice who was a pet beagle?', 'reasoning': 'The information provided mentions that Bill Melendez provided the voices of Snoopy and Woodstock in the "Peanuts" series. Snoopy is a beagle, and Woodstock is a yellow bird. Therefore, Snoopy is the pet beagle that Bill Melendez voiced.', 'answer': 'Snoopy'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Flat-Coated Retriever | The Flat-Coated Retriever is a gundog breed originating from the United Kingdom. It was developed as a retriever both on land and in the water.', 'Bruno Jura Hound | The Bruno Jura hound is a domestic dog, developed in the Middle Ages for hunting in the Jura Mountains on the Swiss-French border.', 'Curly Coated Retriever | The Curly Coated Retriever (often referred to as a Curly) is a breed of dog originally bred in England for upland bird and waterfowl hunting. It is the tallest of the retrievers and is easily distinguishable by the mass of tight curls covering its body. Curly Coated and Wavy Coated (now known as the Flat-Coated Retriever) were the first two recognised retriever breeds, established as early as 1860.'], 'question': 'Are the Flat-Coated Retriever and Bruno Jura Hound both natives of Europe ?', 'reasoning': 'To determine if both the Flat-Coated Retriever and the Bruno Jura Hound are natives of Europe, we need to consider their geographical origins based on the information provided.\n\n1. For the Flat-Coated Retriever, the context states: "Flat-Coated Retriever | The Flat-Coated Retriever is a gundog breed originating from the United Kingdom." The United Kingdom is a country in Europe, so the Flat-Coated Retriever is a native of Europe.\n\n2. For the Bruno Jura Hound, the context provides: "Bruno Jura Hound | The Bruno Jura hound is a domestic dog, developed in the Middle Ages for hunting in the Jura Mountains on the Swiss-French border." Both Switzerland and France have territories in Europe, indicating that the Bruno Jura Hound\'s development occurred in Europe.\n\nSince both breeds can be traced back to geographical locations in Europe, we can conclude that both the Flat-Coated Retriever and the Bruno Jura Hound are natives of Europe.', 'answer': 'Yes'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Telemark (waltz) | The Telemark is a silver level waltz ballroom dance step. Telemarks are reverse turns where the follower does a heel turn as the leader travels around her. There are similar Telemarks in Foxtrot and Quickstep.', 'Quickstep | The quickstep is a light-hearted member of the standard ballroom dances. The movement of the dance is fast and powerfully flowing and sprinkled with syncopations. The upbeat melodies that quickstep is danced to make it suitable for both formal and informal events. Quickstep was developed in the twenties in New York and was first danced by Caribbean and African dancers. Its origins are in combination of slow foxtrot combined with the Charleston, a dance which was one of the precursors to what today is called swing dancing.', 'V6 (Quickstep) | V6 is a "silver" level dance pattern of the quickstep International Standard Ballroom dance syllabus. The couple moves diagonally to the center (DC) and then diagonally to the wall (DW), thus sweeping a V-shape on the floor.', 'Telemark skiing | Telemark skiing, or teleskiing, is a skiing technique that combines elements of Alpine and Nordic skiing. Telemark skiing is named after the Telemark region of Norway, where the discipline originated . Sondre Norheim is often credited for first demonstrating the turn in ski races, which included cross country, slalom and jumping, in Norway around 1868. Sondre Norheim also experimented with ski and binding design, introducing side cuts to skis and heel bindings (like a cable).', 'Electrostep | Electrostep is a genre of syncopated music very similar to dubstep, the main difference being BPM, drum beat, and the general tone of the music.'], 'question': 'What genre does Telemark and Quickstep have in common?', 'reasoning': 'From the given context, Telemark is described as a dance step in the waltz, a type of ballroom dance. On the other hand, Quickstep is explicitly mentioned as a part of the standard ballroom dances. Therefore, the common genre between Telemark and Quickstep is that they are both part of the ballroom dance repertoire, which is a form of dance performance. However, the question might be misleading as it seems to conflate dance categories (e.g., Telemark, Quickstep) with musical genres like ballroom music. Nonetheless, the dance forms commonly performed to ballroom music are in question.', 'answer': 'ballroom dance'}) (input_keys=None)]

